  # All Flux AI Models: Schnell vs Dev vs Pro vs Max
  
  From the 2-credit Schnell to the 25-credit FLUX.2 \[max\] — every Flux AI model from Black Forest Labs compared.
  
  Black Forest Labs has released 10 Flux AI models since August 2024, each targeting a different balance of speed, quality, and price. The lineup ranges from FLUX Schnell (2 credits, sub-second generation) to FLUX.2 Max (25 credits, maximum quality and resolution). Understanding which Flux model to use can save significant credits without sacrificing output quality.
  
  The Flux family splits into three tiers. Budget models (Schnell, Klein, Dev) generate fast at 2-5 credits and work well for drafts, testing prompts, and high-volume workflows. Mid-range models (Flex, Pro, FLUX.2 Pro) add better prompt adherence, higher resolution, and editing capabilities at 6-12 credits. Premium models (Ultra, Kontext, Kontext Max, FLUX.2 Max) deliver the best quality with 4K output, character consistency across images, and advanced editing at 15-25 credits.
  
  All 10 Flux models are available on Melies with shared credits. Generate the same prompt across Schnell and Max to see the quality difference, or use Schnell for iteration and switch to Pro for final output.
  
  Updated May 2026
  
  ## Quick Recommendation
  
  Start with Flux Schnell (2 credits) for the best value. When quality matters more than cost, step up to Flux Kontext Max (25 credits). All 10 models are available on Melies — try each with the same prompt and compare.
  
